    All Classes and Interfaces

    Classes
    Class
    Description
    Cave
    Class represents caves in the game.
    Creature
    Abstract Class which contains a creature used within the game.
    Enemies
    Class which stores enemy creatures.
    EnemyCreature
    Class which stores an enemy creature.
    Fellowship
    Class which stores the Fellowship and the Fellowship Members and their location and location history.
    FellowshipCreature
    Class which stores a creature of the Fellowship.
    FellowshipOfCode
    Class which heads the game Fellowship of Code
    FileOperations
    Class which executes file operations.
    FloppyDisk
    Class which stores the Floppy Disk
    GameConstants
    Class which holds public constants used by several classes
    GameLocation
    Abstract Class which represents a game location.
    GameParts
    Class which store the parts of the game and handle the interaction between them.
    GameRunner
    Class which runs the game Fellowship of Code
    GameTester
    Class which is used to test game classes
    Labyrinth
    Class which stores the structure and location of the game's labyrinth.
    MountApi
    Inherited Class which stores the location of Mount Api
    Namer
    Class which manages available location and character names For orc names see @see https://neoencyclopedia.fandom.com/wiki/List_of_Middle-earth_Orcs For other creature names see @see https://www.writtenwithlove.com.au/blogs/written-with-love-the-journal/100-most-popular-baby-boy-names-for-2024-in-australia For cave names see * @see https://www.merriam-webster.com/thesaurus/doom
    PortableGameObject
    Abstract Class which holds a game object that can be carried by a character
    TextDisplay
    Class which implements GameInteraction to provide user interaction.
    Wizard
    Class which holds the Wizard creature.
